
[1]dispensatory

   DISPENSATORY, n. [L.] One whose employment is to deal out or
   distribute; a distributor; a dispenser; the latter word is generally
   used.

   DISPENSATORY, a. Having power to grant dispensations.

   DISPENSATORY, n. A book containing the method of preparing the various
   kinds of medicines used in pharmacy, or containing directions for the
   composition of medicines, with the proportions of the ingredients, and
   the methods of preparing them.
